              adenocarcinoma, small tumor mass, no-metastasis of the lymph
              node, no-invasion of regional tissues, and TNM I or II stage
              disease than in cases having poorly-differentiated
              adenocarcinoma, large tumor mass, with metastasis and invasion,
              and TNM stage III or IV stage disease (p < 0.01). Univariate
              Kaplan-Meier analysis showed that B2M overexpression (p < 0.001),
              but lack of ALK7 expression (p < 0.001) was significantly
              associated with shorter overall survival. Cox multivariate
              analysis showed that differentiation, tumor mass, lymph node
              metastasis, invasion, TNM stage, and B2M levels negatively
              correlated with overall survival. In contrast, ALK7 level
              positively correlated with overall survival. Positive B2M and
              negative ALK7 expression are poor prognostic factors in PDAC
              patients. CONCLUSIONS: B2M and ALK7 might be important biological
              markers involved in the carcinogenesis, metastasis, invasion, and
              prognosis of PDAC.},
